    "# Module 2: How Browsers Work & Introduction to HTML\n",
    "\n",
    "In this module, we‚Äôll understand how a browser interprets code, how HTML defines page structure, and what happens from HTML input to visual rendering.\n",
    "\n",
    "### üß† What Is a Browser Engine?\n",
    "A browser engine is the software component responsible for:\n",
    "- Parsing HTML/CSS\n",
    "- Laying out elements on screen\n",
    "- Handling JavaScript execution\n",
    "\n",
    "**Major engines include:**\n",
    "- Blink (Chrome, Opera)\n",
    "- WebKit (Safari)\n",
    "- Gecko (Firefox)\n",
    "\n",
    "### ‚öôÔ∏è Rendering Pipeline\n",
    "1. **HTML Tokenization** ‚Üí DOM Tree\n",
    "2. **CSS Parsing** ‚Üí CSSOM Tree\n",
    "3. **DOM + CSSOM** ‚Üí Render Tree\n",
    "4. **Layout** ‚Üí Elements get positions/sizes\n",
    "5. **Painting** ‚Üí Drawing pixels\n",
    "6. **Compositing** ‚Üí Layers combined to screen\n",
    "\n",
    "### üß± Introduction to HTML\n",
    "**HTML (HyperText Markup Language)** is the backbone of any webpage. It defines content structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Basic Tags:**\n",
    "```html\n",
    "<!DOCTYPE html>\n",
    "<html>\n",
    "  <head>\n",
    "    <title>My Page</title>\n",
    "  </head>\n",
    "  <body>\n",
    "    <h1>Hello, world!</h1>\n",
    "  </body>\n",
    "</html>\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Common HTML Elements:**\n",
    "- `<h1>` to `<h6>`: Headings\n",
    "- `<p>`: Paragraph\n",
    "- `<img src=\"\">`: Images\n",
    "- `<a href=\"\">`: Links\n",
    "- `<div>`: Division (container)\n",
    "- `<span>`: Inline container\n",
    "- `<form>`: Input handling\n",
    "\n",
    "### üß≠ Semantic HTML\n",
    "Semantic elements convey meaning:\n",
    "- `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<main>`, `<nav>` improve accessibility and SEO.\n",
    "\n",
    "### üß™ Developer Tools\n",
    "Inspect live web pages using Chrome DevTools:\n",
    "- Right-click ‚Üí Inspect\n",
    "- See DOM in real time\n",
    "- Modify and test HTML/CSS live\n",
    "\n",
    "### üß† Accessibility & Structure\n",
    "Use correct HTML structure for:\n",
    "- Screen readers (aria-labels, roles)\n",
    "- SEO (search engines rely on heading tags)\n",
    "- Responsive design (semantic containers adapt better)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
